[30083.459635, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[H\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;231m\u001b[1mWhere does the contract schema (.fbs + generated Rust/TS) live? Branch 1 \u001b[22m\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;231m\u001b[1mexpected a module under interfaces/clyffy-brain, but DevPulse (Tauri/Svelte) \r\u001b[1Bmust consume the same schema, which argues for a shared home.\u001b[22m\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;153m❯\u001b[3G\u001b[38;5;246m1.\u001b[6G\u001b[38;5;153mNew clyffy-protocol crate (Recommended)\r\u001b[1B\u001b[39m     \u001b[38;5;246mTop-level workspace crate owning the .fbs sources + codegen (Rust now, TS \r\u001b[1B\u001b[39m     \u001b[38;5;246mfor DevPulse). Supersedes branch 1's module-in-brain note (named, per the \r\u001b[5C\u001b[1Brule) — a schema consumed by both brain and client is a real boundary. \r\u001b[1B\u001b[39m \u001b[3G  \u001b[6G\u001b[38;5;246mNeeds the COSTAR gate per PLANNING_DISCIPLINE.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B2.\u001b[6G\u001b[39mModule in interfaces/clyffy-brain\u001b[K\r\u001b[5C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;246mKeep branc\u001b[18G1'\u001b[22Gexpectati\u001b[32Gn: schema + codegen inside t\u001b[61Ge brain binary \u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[6C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;246mrate. No new crate/COSTAR\u001b[33Ggate, but DevPulse must\u001b[57Gr\u001b[60Gch into a\u001b[71Ginary \u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[5C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;246mcrate's guts\u001b[19G(\u001b[21Gr \u001b[24Gopy files) for TS codegen — smells like scatter.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B3\u001b[6G\u001b[39mIn th\u001b[13Gconnectom\u001b[23G fork\r\u001b[5C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;246mExtend connectome-protocol in ~/Projec\u001b[45Gs/c\u001b[49Gnnectome\u001b[59GRejected-by-default: \r\u001b[5C\u001b[1Bpoll\u001b[11Gtes the clea\u001b[24G fork with clyffy-sp\u001b[45Gcific frames (\u001b[60Glean-fo\u001b[68Gk law),\u001b[76Gand \r\u001b[5C\u001b[1Bthe fo\u001b[13Gk vendors ge\u001b[27Grated\u001b[33Gcode only.\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;246m4\r\u001b[2C\u001b[2B\u001b[39m5\u001b[23;1H\u001b[6;1H\u001b[?2026l"]
[30088.326061, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[H\u001b[38;5;246m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\r\u001b[1B\u001b[39m←  ☒ Converse path  ☒ Stream map  ☒ Schema home \u001b[48;5;153m\u001b[38;5;16m ☐ Build scope \u001b[39m\u001b[49m ✔ Submit \u001b[75G→\r\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;231m\u001b[1mExecution scope for this pl\u001b[29Gn\u001b[31G— what should actually get built when it runs?\r\u001b[5C\u001b[2B\u001b[22m\u001b[38;5;153mContract + skelet\u001b[24Gn\u001b[26G+ bench (Recommen\u001b[44Ged)\r\u001b[5C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;246mAuthor the contr\u001b[24Gt\u001b[26Gdoc +\u001b[32G.fbs schema + control-plane endpoint \u001b[70Gkeletons \u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[5C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;246m(axum ro\u001b[15Gtes ret\u001b[23Grning typed stubs) + the bra\u001b[52Gch-1 be\u001b[60Gchmark harness \u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[5C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;246m(F\u001b[9GatBuffers-over-TCP vs QUIC \u001b[37Gn the real LAN). No\u001b[57Gfull\u001b[62Gs\u001b[64Gssion engine\u001b[77Gyet \r\u001b[5C\u001b[1B— that's the fold's build\u001b[32Gplan.\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[5C\u001b[1BSpec/docs\u001b[16Go\u001b[18Gly\u001b[K\r\u001b[5C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;246mWrite the contract spec d\u001b[32Gcument and .fbs schema only; zero code changes. \r\u001b[5C\u001b[1BCheapest,\u001b[16Gpurely paper — but nothing\u001b[43Gv\u001b[45Grifiable end-to-end, ag\u001b[69Ginst the \r\u001b[5C\u001b[1Boperator-verifies-each-pha\u001b[33Ge\u001b[35Gpractice.\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[5C\u001b[1BFull v1 slice\u001b[K\r\u001b[5C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;246mContract + s\u001b[19Ghe\u001b[22Ga + endp\u001b[31Gints\u001b[36G+ conn\u001b[45Gome sessi\u001b[55Gn/outbox/journal tables + \r\u001b[5C\u001b[1BQUIC upgrad\u001b[19G+ attach/replay\u001b[35Gworking end-to-end. The whole branch 2+3\u001b[76G\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[5C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;246msurface in one plan — big;\u001b[33Gprobably belongs to the fold, not this branch.\u001b[39m\u001b[23;1H\u001b[6;1H\u001b[?2026l"]
[30092.61591, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[H\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;246m────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\r\u001b[1B\u001b[39m←\u001b[4G☒\u001b[6GConverse\u001b[15Gpath\u001b[21G☒\u001b[23GStream\u001b[30Gmap\u001b[35G☒\u001b[37GSchema\u001b[44Ghome\u001b[50G☒\u001b[52GBuild\u001b[58Gscope\u001b[64G\u001b[48;5;153m\u001b[38;5;16m ✔ Submit \u001b[49m\u001b[38;5;246m →\r\u001b[1B\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;231m\u001b[1mReview your answers\r\u001b[1B\u001b[22m\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[1C\u001b[1B●\u001b[4GWhere does /converse live once a client is attached — does chat ride the QUIC\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1Bfast path with outbox replay, or stay HTTP+SSE as today?\u001b[K\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;114m→ Fast path + outbox (Recommended)\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[1C\u001b[1B●\u001b[4GIngestion stream layout on the QUIC\u001b[40Gconnection\u001b[51G—\u001b[53Gone\u001b[57Gstream\u001b[64Gper\u001b[68Gsource,\u001b[76Gor\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B one muxed \u001b[15Gtream?\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;114m→ Per-source streams (Recommended)\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[1C\u001b[1B●\u001b[4GWhere does the contract schema (.fbs + generated Rust/TS) live? Branch 1\u001b[K\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1Bexpected a module under interfaces/clyffy-brain,\u001b[53Gbut\u001b[57GDevPulse\u001b[66G(Tauri/Svelte)\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B must consume the\u001b[21Gsame\u001b[26Gschema,\u001b[34Gwhich\u001b[40Gargues\u001b[47Gfor\u001b[51Ga\u001b[53Gshared\u001b[60Ghome.\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;114m→ New clyffy-protocol crate (Recommended)\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[1C\u001b[1B●\u001b[4GExecution scope for this plan — what should actually get built when it runs?\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;114m→ Contract + skeleton + bench (Recommended)\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;246mReady to submit your answers?\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;153m❯\u001b[3G\u001b[38;5;246m1. \u001