[33062.071166, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\u001b[48;5;237m\u001b[38;5;239m❯ you then because of the incomplete work need to get the full event done loop…\u001b[39m \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[49m\u001b[1mcount\u001b[22m (N=1\u001b[14Gbeats N=16 — one connec\u001b[38Gion = on\u001b[47G crypto/pacing pipeline).\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BIrrelevant\u001b[14Gwhen\u001b[19Glink-capped,\u001b[32Gbut\u001b[36Git's\u001b[41Gthe\u001b[45Gper-connection\u001b[60Gceiling\u001b[68Gto\u001b[71Gremember.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BAnd\u001b[7Gto close\u001b[16Gthe loop \u001b[26Gn your\u001b[33Gquestion:\u001b[43Gy\u001b[45Gs —\u001b[49Gyour \u001b[55Gystems all keep working.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BThe embedded high-performanc\u001b[32G ingestion\u001b[43Gnev\u001b[48G leaves clyffy; the wire only\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bdelivers\u001b[15Gtext, the measured floor is\u001b[43Gorders of\u001b[53Gmagnitude above what the\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bpipelin\u001b[11G consumes, and journal-then-ACK means the worst\u001b[59Ga bad conn\u001b[70Gction\u001b[76Gcan\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bdo\u001b[6Gis\u001b[9Gdelay\u001b[15G\u001b[3mnew\u001b[19G\u001b[23mcontext\u001b[27G—\u001b[29Git\u001b[32Gcan\u001b[36Gnever\u001b[42Gstall\u001b[48Gor\u001b[51Gdegrade\u001b[59Gclyffy\u001b[66Gitself.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BOnly the real-LAN \u001b[22Geg\u001b[25G(devstation ↔\u001b[39Gclyffy-01) remains, and it needs the\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bdevstation physically\u001b[25Gonline\u001b[32G—\u001b[34Git's\u001b[39Grecorded\u001b[48Gas\u001b[51Gthe\u001b[55Gopen\u001b[60Ggate\u001b[65Gcell\u001b[70Gin\u001b[73Gthe\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bnotes\u001b[9Gfor\u001b[13Gthe\u001b[17Gfold.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BYou\u001b[7Gcan\u001b[11Gclose\u001b[17Gthis\u001b[22Gsessi\u001b[48;5;237m\u001b[38;5;231m Jump to bottom (ctrl+End) ↓ \u001b[57G\u001b[39m\u001b[49m4\u001b[59G(deployment-shape).\u001b[23;1H\u001b[19;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
[33062.093358, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Blatency (\u001b[13G7µs) \u001b[19Gits at TLS-TCP l\u001b[36Gvel.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- One real\u001b[14Gfinding for th\u001b[29G fold:\u001b[36G\u001b[1mQUIC throughput doesn't scale with stream \u001b[22m\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[1mcount\u001b[9G\u001b[22m(N=1\u001b[14Gbeats\u001b[20GN=16\u001b[25G—\u001b[27Gone\u001b[31Gconnection\u001b[42G=\u001b[44Gone\u001b[48Gcrypto/pacing\u001b[62Gpipeline).\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BIrrelevant when link-capped, but i\u001b[38G's the per-c\u001b[51Gnnection cei\u001b[64Ging to\u001b[71Gremember.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BAnd to close the loop\u001b[25Gon your question:\u001b[43Gyes — y\u001b[51Gur systems all k\u001b[68Gep working.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BThe emb\u001b[11Gdded high-performance ing\u001b[37Gstion\u001b[43Gn\u001b[45Gver\u001b[49Gleaves clyffy; the wire \u001b[75Gly\u001b[K\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1Bel\u001b[7Gvers context, th\u001b[24G measured floor is orders of magnitude above what\u001b[74Gthe\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bpipeline\u001b[12Gconsumes,\u001b[22Gand\u001b[26Gjournal-then-ACK\u001b[43Gmeans\u001b[49Gthe\u001b[53Gworst\u001b[59Ga\u001b[61Gbad\u001b[65Gconnection\u001b[76Gcan\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bdo is d\u001b[11Glay \u001b[3mnew\u001b[23m context — i\u001b[31G can never stall or degrade\u001b[59Gclyffy\u001b[66Gitself.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BOnly the real-LAN leg\u001b[25G(devstation\u001b[37G↔\u001b[39Gclyffy-01)\u001b[50Gremains,\u001b[59Gand\u001b[63Git\u001b[66Gneeds\u001b[72Gthe\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bdevstation\u001b[14Gphysically\u001b[25Gonline\u001b[32G—\u001b[34Git's\u001b[39Grecorded\u001b[48Gas\u001b[51Gthe\u001b[55Gopen\u001b[60Ggate\u001b[65Gcell\u001b[70Gin\u001b[73Gthe\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bn\u001b[5Gtes for th\u001b[17Gfold.     \u001b[57G\u001b[K\u001b[23;1H\u001b[19;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
[33062.118187, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BTCP 253\u001b[11G→ TLS-TCP 142 Gbps at N=16/64KB),\u001b[45Gso\u001b[48GQUIC's\u001b[55Gremaining\u001b[65Ggap\u001b[69Gis\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Btra\u001b[7Gsport-structural (per-datagram userspace work), not crypto. QUIC's p50\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Blatency (\u001b[13G7µs) \u001b[19Gits at TLS-TCP l\u001b[36Gvel.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- One real\u001b[14Gfinding for th\u001b[29G fold:\u001b[36G\u001b[1mQUIC throughput doesn't scale with stream \u001b[22m\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[1mcount\u001b[9G\u001b[22m(N=1\u001b[14Gbeats\u001b[20GN=16\u001b[25G—\u001b[27Gone\u001b[31Gconnection\u001b[42G=\u001b[44Gone\u001b[48Gcrypto/pacing\u001b[62Gpipeline).\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BIrrelevant when link-capped, but i\u001b[38G's the per-c\u001b[51Gnnection cei\u001b[64Ging to\u001b[71Gremember.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BAnd to close the loop\u001b[25Gon your question:\u001b[43Gyes — y\u001b[51Gur systems all k\u001b[68Gep working.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BThe emb\u001b[11Gdded high-performance ing\u001b[37Gstion\u001b[43Gn\u001b[45Gver\u001b[49Gleaves clyffy; the wire \u001b[75Gly\u001b[K\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1Bel\u001b[7Gvers context, th\u001b[24G measured floor is orders of magnitude above what\u001b[74Gthe\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bpipeline\u001b[12Gconsumes,\u001b[22Gand\u001b[26Gjournal-then-ACK\u001b[43Gmeans\u001b[49Gthe\u001b[53Gworst\u001b[59Ga\u001b[61Gbad\u001b[65Gconnection\u001b[76Gcan\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bdo is d\u001b[11Glay \u001b[3mnew\u001b[23m context — i\u001b[31G can never stall or degrade\u001b[59Gclyffy\u001b[66Gitself.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BOnly the real-LAN leg\u001b[25G(d\u001b[56Gs,\u001b[59Gand\u001b[63Git\u001b[66Gneeds\u001b[72Gthe\u001b[23;1H\u001b[19;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
[33062.493883, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- \u001b[1mThe rustls-TCP reference lane did its job:\u001b[48G\u001b[22mcrypto\u001b[55Galone costs ~45%\u001b[72G(plain\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BTCP 253 → TLS-TCP 142 Gbps \u001b[32G N=16/64KB), so\u001b[48GQUIC's\u001b[55Gremaining gap is\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Btransport-structural (per-datagram userspace\u001b[48Gwork),\u001b[55Gnot\u001b[59Gcrypto.\u001b[67GQUIC's\u001b[74Gp50\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Blatency (17µs) sits at\u001b[26GTLS-TCP level.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- One\u001b[9Greal\u001b[14Gfinding for the fold: \u001b[1mQUIC throughput doesn't scale with stream \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bcount\u001b[22m (N=1\u001b[14Gbeats N=16 — one connec\u001b[38Gion = on\u001b[47G crypto/pacing pipeline).\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BIrrelevant\u001b[14Gwhen\u001b[19Glink-capped,\u001b[32Gbut\u001b[36Git's\u001b[41Gthe\u001b[45Gper-connection\u001b[60Gceiling\u001b[68Gto\u001b[71Gremember.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BAnd\u001b[7Gto close\u001b[16Gthe loop \u001b[26Gn your\u001b[33Gquestion:\u001b[43Gy\u001b[45Gs —\u001b[49Gyour \u001b[55Gystems all keep working.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BThe embedded high-performanc\u001b[32G ingestion\u001b[43Gnev\u001b[48G leaves clyffy; the wire only\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bdelivers\u001b[15Gtext, the measured floor is\u001b[43Gorders of\u001b[53Gmagnitude above what the\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bpipelin\u001b[11G consumes, and journal-then-ACK means the worst\u001b[59Ga bad conn\u001b[70Gction\u001b[76Gcan\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bdo\u001b[6Gis\u001b[9Gdelay\u001b[15G\u001b[3mnew\u001b[19G\u001b[23mcontext\u001b[27G—\u001b[29Git\u001b[32Gcan\u001b[36Gnever\u001b[42Gstall\u001b[48Gor\u001b[51Gdegrade\u001b[59Gclyffy\u001b[66Gitself.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B    \u001b[8G   \u001b[12G        \u001b[21G   \u001b[25G  \u001b[56G\u001b[K\u001b[23;1H\u001b[19;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
[33062.509565, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bthe LAN leg decides when the devstation is online.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- \u001b[1mThe rustls-TCP reference lane did its job:\u001b[48G\u001b[22mcrypto\u001b[55Galone costs ~45%\u001b[72G(plain\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BTCP 253 → TLS-TCP 142 Gbps \u001b[32G N=16/64KB), so\u001b[48GQUIC's\u001b[55Gremaining gap is\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Btransport-structural (per-datagram userspace\u001b[48Gwork),\u001b[55Gnot\u001b[59Gcrypto.\u001b[67GQUIC's\u001b[74Gp50\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Blatency (17µs) sits at\u001b[26GTLS-TCP level.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- One\u001b[9Greal\u001b[14Gfinding for the fold: \u001b[1mQUIC throughput doesn't scale with stream \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bcount\u001b[22m (N=1\u001b[14Gbeats N=16 — one connec\u001b[38Gion = on\u001b[47G crypto/pacing pipeline).\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BIrrelevant\u001b[14Gwhen\u001b[19Glink-capped,\u001b[32Gbut\u001b[36Git's\u001b[41Gthe\u001b[45Gper-connection\u001b[60Gceiling\u001b[68Gto\u001b[71Gremember.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BAnd\u001b[7Gto close\u001b[16Gthe loop \u001b[26Gn your\u001b[33Gquestion:\u001b[43Gy\u001b[45Gs —\u001b[49Gyour \u001b[55Gystems all keep working.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BThe embedded high-performanc\u001b[32G ingestion\u001b[43Gnev\u001b[48G leaves clyffy; the wire only\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bdelivers\u001b[15Gtext, the measured floor is\u001b[43Gorders of\u001b[53Gmagnitude above what the\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bpipelin\u001b[11G consumes, and journal-then-ACK means the worst\u001b[59Ga bad conn\u001b[70Gction\u001b[76Gcan\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bdo\u001b[6Gis\u001b[9Gdelay\u001b[15G\u001b[3mnew\u001b[19G\u001b[23mcontext\u001b[56Gde\u001b[59Gclyffy\u001b[66Gitself.\u001b[23;1H\u001b[19;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
[33062.517639, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Binterestin\u001b[15G(QUIC would land\u001b[32G~50–80% \u001b[41Gf\u001b[43Gline rat\u001b[52G),\u001b[55Gand\u001b[59Gthat's\u001b[66Gexactly\u001b[74Gwhat\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bthe LAN leg decides when the devstation is online.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- \u001b[1mThe rustls-TCP reference lane did its job:\u001b[48G\u001b[22mcrypto\u001b[55Galone costs ~45%\u001b[72G(plain\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BTCP 253 → TLS-TCP 142 Gbps \u001b[32G N=16/64KB), so\u001b[48GQUIC's\u001b[55Gremaining gap is\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Btransport-structural (per-datagram userspace\u001b[48Gwork),\u001b[55Gnot\u001b[59Gcrypto.\u001b[67GQUIC's\u001b[74Gp50\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Blatency (17µs) sits at\u001b[26GTLS-TCP level.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- One\u001b[9Greal\u001b[14Gfinding for the fold: \u001b[1mQUIC throughput doesn't scale with stream \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bcount\u001b[22m (N=1\u001b[14Gbeats N=16 — one connec\u001b[38Gion = on\u001b[47G crypto/pacing pipeline).\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BIrrelevant\u001b[14Gwhen\u001b[19Glink-capped,\u001b[32Gbut\u001b[36Git's\u001b[41Gthe\u001b[45Gper-connection\u001b[60Gceiling\u001b[68Gto\u001b[71Gremember.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BAnd\u001b[7Gto close\u001b[16Gthe loop \u001b[26Gn your\u001b[33Gquestion:\u001b[43Gy\u001b[45Gs —\u001b[49Gyour \u001b[55Gystems all keep working.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BThe embedded high-performanc\u001b[32G ingestion\u001b[43Gnev\u001b[48G leaves clyffy; the wire only\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bdelivers\u001b[15Gtext, the measured floor is\u001b[43Gorders of\u001b[53Gmagnitude above what the\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bpipelin\u001b[11G consumes, and j\u001b[56Gst\u001b[59Ga bad conn\u001b[70Gction\u001b[76Gcan\u001b[23;1H\u001b[19;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
[33062.536395, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B1/2.5/5GbE devstati\u001b[23Gn link outright.\u001b[40GOnly a 10GbE link makes th\u001b[67G ga\u001b[71Ge\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Binterestin\u001b[15G(QUIC would land\u001b[32G~50–80% \u001b[41Gf\u001b[43Gline rat\u001b[52G),\u001b[55Gand\u001b[59Gthat's\u001b[66Gexactly\u001b[74Gwhat\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bthe LAN leg decides when the devstation is online.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- \u001b[1mThe rustls-TCP reference lane did its job:\u001b[48G\u001b[22mcrypto\u001b[55Galone costs ~45%\u001b[72G(plain\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BTCP 253 → TLS-TCP 142 Gbps \u001b[32G N=16/64KB), so\u001b[48GQUIC's\u001b[55Gremaining gap is\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Btransport-structural (per-datagram userspace\u001b[48Gwork),\u001b[55Gnot\u001b[59Gcrypto.\u001b[67GQUIC's\u001b[74Gp50\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Blatency (17µs) sits at\u001b[26GTLS-TCP level.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- One\u001b[9Greal\u001b[14Gfinding for the fold: \u001b[1mQUIC throughput doesn't scale with stream \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bcount\u001b[22m (N=1\u001b[14Gbeats N=16 — one connec\u001b[38Gion = on\u001b[47G crypto/pacing pipeline).\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BIrrelevant\u001b[14Gwhen\u001b[19Glink-capped,\u001b[32Gbut\u001b[36Git's\u001b[41Gthe\u001b[45Gper-connection\u001b[60Gceiling\u001b[68Gto\u001b[71Gremember.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BAnd\u001b[7Gto close\u001b[16Gthe loop \u001b[26Gn your\u001b[33Gquestion:\u001b[43Gy\u001b[45Gs —\u001b[49Gyour \u001b[55Gystems all keep working.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BThe embedded high-performanc\u001b[32G ingestion\u001b[43Gnev\u001b[48G leaves clyffy; the wire only\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bdelivers\u001b[15Gtext, the me\u001b[56Gnitude above what the\u001b[K\u001b[23;1H\u001b[19;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
[33062.541031, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[1mWhat the full matrix settled:\u001b[22m\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- \u001b[1mQUIC's floor is 5–8 Gbps (600–1000 MB/s) in every bulk cell\u001b[22m — it saturates\u001b[80Ga\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B1/2.5/5GbE devstation link outright. O\u001b[42Gly a 10GbE link\u001b[58Gmakes\u001b[64Gthe\u001b[68Ggate\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Binteresting (QUIC would land ~50–80% of line\u001b[48Grate),\u001b[56Gnd that's exactly what\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bthe\u001b[7GLAN\u001b[11Gleg decides when the devstation is \u001b[47Gnline.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- \u001b[1mThe rustls-TCP reference lane did its job:\u001b[48G\u001b[22mcrypto\u001b[55Galone costs\u001b[67G~45% (plain\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BTCP 253\u001b[11G→ TLS-TCP 142 Gbps at N=16/64KB),\u001b[45Gso\u001b[48GQUIC's\u001b[55Gremaining\u001b[65Ggap\u001b[69Gis\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Btra\u001b[7Gsport-structural (per-datagram userspace work), not crypto. QUIC's p50\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Blatency (\u001b[13G7µs) \u001b[19Gits at TLS-TCP l\u001b[36Gvel.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- One real\u001b[14Gfinding for th\u001b[29G fold:\u001b[36G\u001b[1mQUIC throughput doesn't scale with stream \u001b[22m\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[1mcount\u001b[9G\u001b[22m(N=1\u001b[14Gbeats\u001b[20GN=16\u001b[25G—\u001b[27Gone\u001b[31Gconnection\u001b[42G=\u001b[44Gone\u001b[48Gcrypto/pacing\u001b[62Gpipeline).\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BIrrelevant when link-capped, but i\u001b[38G's the per-c\u001b[51Gnnection cei\u001b[64Ging to\u001b[71Gremember.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BAnd to close the loop\u001b[25Gon\u001b[56Gstems all k\u001b[68Gep working.\u001b[23;1H\u001b[19;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
[33062.557349, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bcarry the finding.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[1mWhat the full matrix settled:\u001b[22m\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- \u001b[1mQUIC's floor is 5–8 Gbps (600–1000 MB/s) in every bulk cell\u001b[22m — it saturates\u001b[80Ga\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B1/2.5/5GbE devstation link outright. O\u001b[42Gly a 10GbE link\u001b[58Gmakes\u001b[64Gthe\u001b[68Ggate\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Binteresting (QUIC would land ~50–80% of line\u001b[48Grate),\u001b[56Gnd that's exactly what\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bthe\u001b[7GLAN\u001b[11Gleg decides when the devstation is \u001b[47Gnline.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- \u001b[1mThe rustls-TCP reference lane did its job:\u001b[48G\u001b[22mcrypto\u001b[55Galone costs\u001b[67G~45% (plain\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BTCP 253\u001b[11G→ TLS-TCP 142 Gbps at N=16/64KB),\u001b[45Gso\u001b[48GQUIC's\u001b[55Gremaining\u001b[65Ggap\u001b[69Gis\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Btra\u001b[7Gsport-structural (per-datagram userspace work), not crypto. QUIC's p50\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Blatency (\u001b[13G7µs) \u001b[19Gits at TLS-TCP l\u001b[36Gvel.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- One real\u001b[14Gfinding for th\u001b[29G fold:\u001b[36G\u001b[1mQUIC throughput doesn't scale with stream \u001b[22m\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[1mcount\u001b[9G\u001b[22m(N=1\u001b[14Gbeats\u001b[20GN=16\u001b[25G—\u001b[27Gone\u001b[31Gconnection\u001b[42G=\u001b[44Gone\u001b[48Gcrypto/pacing\u001b[62Gpipeline).\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BIrrelevant when link-cap\u001b[56Gion cei\u001b[64Ging to\u001b[71Gremember.\u001b[23;1H\u001b[19;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
[33062.58893, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;231m●\u001b[3G\u001b[39mThe full loopback event\u001b[27Gis\u001b[30Gdone\u001b[35Gand\u001b[39Geverything\u001b[50Gis\u001b[53Gfolded\u001b[60Gin.\u001b[64GThe\u001b[68Gcomplete\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B33-cell\u001b[11Gmatrix\u001b[18Gis\u001b[21Gin\u001b[24G\u001b[38;5;153mJOURNAL.md\u001b[39m,\u001b[36Gand\u001b[40Gthe\u001b[44Gdive\u001b[49Gnotes\u001b[55G+\u001b[57Gevolving\u001b[66Gmemory\u001b[73Gnow\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bcarry the finding.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[1mWhat the full matrix settled:\u001b[22m\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- \u001b[1mQUIC's floor is 5–8 Gbps (600–1000 MB/s) in every bulk cell\u001b[22m — it saturates\u001b[80Ga\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B1/2.5/5GbE devstation link outright. O\u001b[42Gly a 10GbE link\u001b[58Gmakes\u001b[64Gthe\u001b[68Ggate\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Binteresting (QUIC would land ~50–80% of line\u001b[48Grate),\u001b[56Gnd that's exactly what\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bthe\u001b[7GLAN\u001b[11Gleg decides when the devstation is \u001b[47Gnline.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- \u001b[1mThe rustls-TCP reference lane did its job:\u001b[48G\u001b[22mcrypto\u001b[55Galone costs\u001b[67G~45% (plain\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BTCP 253\u001b[11G→ TLS-TCP 142 Gbps at N=16/64KB),\u001b[45Gso\u001b[48GQUIC's\u001b[55Gremaining\u001b[65Ggap\u001b[69Gis\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Btra\u001b[7Gsport-structural (per-datagram userspace work), not crypto. QUIC's p50\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Blatency (\u001b[13G7µs) \u001b[19Gits at TLS-TCP l\u001b[36Gvel.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- One real\u001b[14Gfinding for t\u001b[56G\u001b[1mn't scale with stream \u001b[22m\u001b[K\u001b[23;1H\u001b[19;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
