[33068.013166, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;246mRead \u001b[1m1\u001b[22m file, ran \u001b[1m1\u001b[22m shell command \r\u001b[1B\u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;231m●\u001b[3G\u001b[39mThe fu\u001b[10Gl loopback\u001b[21Gevent is done and everything is fold\u001b[58Gd in. The c\u001b[70Gmplete\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B33-cell matrix is in\u001b[24G\u001b[38;5;153mJOURNAL.md\u001b[39m,\u001b[36Gand\u001b[40Gthe\u001b[44Gdive\u001b[49Gnotes\u001b[55G+\u001b[57Gevolving\u001b[66Gmemory\u001b[73Gnow\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bcarry\u001b[9Gthe\u001b[13Gfinding.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[1mWhat the\u001b[13Gull matrix settled:\u001b[22m\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- \u001b[1mQUIC's floor is 5–8 Gbps (600–1000 MB/s) in every bulk cell\u001b[22m — it saturates\u001b[80Ga\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B1/2.5/5GbE devstati\u001b[23Gn link outright.\u001b[40GOnly a 10GbE link makes th\u001b[67G ga\u001b[71Ge\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Binterestin\u001b[15G(QUIC would land\u001b[32G~50–80% \u001b[41Gf\u001b[43Gline rat\u001b[52G),\u001b[55Gand\u001b[59Gthat's\u001b[66Gexactly\u001b[74Gwhat\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bthe LAN leg decides when the devstation is online.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- \u001b[1mThe rustls-TCP reference lane did its job:\u001b[48G\u001b[22mcrypto\u001b[55Galone costs ~45%\u001b[72G(plain\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BTCP 253 → TLS-TCP 142 Gbps \u001b[32G N=16/64KB), so\u001b[48GQUIC's\u001b[55Gremaining gap is\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Btransport-structural (pe\u001b[56Got\u001b[59Gcrypto.\u001b[67GQUIC's\u001b[74Gp50\u001b[23;1H\u001b[19;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
