[33072.230976, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\r\u001b[1B  \u001b[38;5;246mRead \u001b[1m1\u001b[22m file \u001b[39m\u001b[K\r\u001b[2B\u001b[38;5;231m●\u001b[3G\u001b[39mFull matrix done\u001b[20G—\u001b[22G33\u001b[25Gcells.\u001b[32GWriting\u001b[40Gthe\u001b[44Gjournal\u001b[52Gtable\u001b[58Gand\u001b[62Gupdating\u001b[71Gthe\u001b[75Gdive\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bnotes/memory.\r\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;246mRead \u001b[1m1\u001b[22m file, ran \u001b[1m1\u001b[22m shell command \r\u001b[2B\u001b[38;5;231m●\u001b[3G\u001b[39mThe full loopback event is done and\u001b[39Geverything\u001b[50Gis\u001b[53Gfolded\u001b[60Gin.\u001b[64GThe\u001b[68Gcomplete\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B33-cell\u001b[11Gmatrix\u001b[18Gis\u001b[21Gin\u001b[24G\u001b[38;5;153mJOURNAL.md\u001b[39m,\u001b[36Gand\u001b[40Gthe\u001b[44Gdive\u001b[49Gnotes\u001b[55G+\u001b[57Gevolving\u001b[66Gmemory\u001b[73Gnow\r\u001b[1B \u001b[3Gcarry the finding.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[1mWhat the full matrix settled:\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[22m-\u001b[5G\u001b[1mQUIC's floor is 5–8 Gbps (600–1000 MB/s) in every bulk cell\u001b[65G\u001b[22m—\u001b[67Git\u001b[70Gsaturates\u001b[80Ga\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B1/2.5/5GbE devstation li\u001b[56Gk\u001b[58Gmakes\u001b[64Gthe\u001b[68Ggate\u001b[23;1H\u001b[19;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
[33072.253645, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;231m●\u001b[3G\u001b[39mThe full loopback\u001b[21Gevent\u001b[27Gis\u001b[30Gdone\u001b[35Gand\u001b[39Geverything\u001b[50Gis\u001b[53Gfolded\u001b[60Gin.\u001b[64GThe\u001b[68Gcomplete\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B33-cell\u001b[11Gmatrix\u001b[18Gis\u001b[21Gin\u001b[24G\u001b[38;5;153mJOURNAL.md\u001b[39m,\u001b[36Gand\u001b[40Gthe\u001b[44Gdive\u001b[49Gnotes\u001b[55G+\u001b[57Gevolving\u001b[66Gmemory\u001b[73Gnow\r\u001b[1B \u001b[3Gcarry the finding.\u001b[22G\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[1mWhat the full matrix settled:\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[22m- \u001b[1mQUIC's floor is 5–8 Gbps (600–1000 MB/s) in every bulk cell\u001b[65G\u001b[22m—\u001b[67Git\u001b[70Gsaturates\u001b[80Ga\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B1/2.5/5GbE\u001b[14Gdevstation\u001b[25Glink\u001b[30Goutright.\u001b[40GOnly\u001b[45Ga\u001b[47G10GbE\u001b[53Glink\u001b[58Gmakes\u001b[64Gthe\u001b[68Ggate\r\u001b[1B \u001b[3Ginteresting (QUIC\u001b[21Gwould\u001b[27Glan\u001b[31G ~50–80% of line rate), and that's \u001b[67Gxactly what\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bthe LAN\u001b[11Gleg dec\u001b[19Gdes when the devstation is online.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- \u001b[1mThe rustls-TCP reference lane did its job:\u001b[48G\u001b[22mcrypto\u001b[55Galone\u001b[61Gcosts\u001b[67G~45%\u001b[72G(plain\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BTCP\u001b[7G253\u001b[11G→\u001b[13GTLS-TCP\u001b[21G142\u001b[25GGbps\u001b[30Gat\u001b[33GN=16/64KB),\u001b[45Gso\u001b[48GQUIC's\u001b[55Gremaining\u001b[65Ggap\u001b[69Gis\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Btransport-structural (per-datagram\u001b[38Guserspace\u001b[48Gwork),\u001b[55Gnot\u001b[59Gcrypto.\u001b[67GQUIC's\u001b[74Gp50\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Blatency (17µs) sits at TLS-TCP level.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- One real\u001b[14Gfinding for t\u001b[56G\u001b[1mn't scale with stream \u001b[22m\u001b[23;1H\u001b[19;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
[33072.258417, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\r\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[1mWhat the full matrix settled:\u001b[22m\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- \u001b[1mQUIC's floor is 5–8 Gbps (600–1000 MB/s) in every bulk cell\u001b[65G\u001b[22m—\u001b[67Git\u001b[70Gsaturates\u001b[80Ga\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B1/2.5/5GbE\u001b[14Gdevstation\u001b[25Glink\u001b[30Goutright.\u001b[40GOnly\u001b[45Ga\u001b[47G10GbE\u001b[53Glink\u001b[58Gmakes\u001b[64Gthe\u001b[68Ggate\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Binteresting (QUIC would land ~50–80%\u001b[40Gof\u001b[43Gline\u001b[48Grate),\u001b[55Gand\u001b[59Gthat's\u001b[66Gexactly\u001b[74Gwhat\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bthe LAN leg decides when the devstation is online.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- \u001b[1mThe rustls-TCP reference lane did its job:\u001b[22m crypto alone cos\u001b[65Gs ~45% (plain\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BTCP 253 → TLS-TCP\u001b[21G142 Gbps at N=16/64KB), so\u001b[48GQUIC's\u001b[55Gremaining gap is\u001b[K\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1Bransport-stru\u001b[18Gtural (per-datagram userspace work),\u001b[55Gnot\u001b[59Gcrypto.\u001b[67GQUIC's\u001b[74Gp50\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Blatency (17µs) sits at TLS-TCP level.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- One real finding for the\u001b[30Gfold: \u001b[1mQUIC throughput doesn't scale with stream \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bcount\u001b[22m (N=1 beats N=16 — one connection = on\u001b[48Gcrypto/pacing \u001b[63Gipeline).\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BIrr\u001b[7Glevant when link-capped, but it's\u001b[41Gthe\u001b[45Gper-connection\u001b[60Gceiling\u001b[68Gto\u001b[71Gremember.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B \u001b[5G   \u001b[9G    \u001b[14G       \u001b[22G   \u001b[26G \u001b[56G\u001b[K\u001b[23;1H\u001b[19;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
[33072.551856, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[1mWhat the full matrix settled:\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[22m- \u001b[1mQUIC's\u001b[13Gloor is 5–8 Gbps (600–1000 MB/s) in every bulk cell\u001b[65G\u001b[22m—\u001b[67Git\u001b[70Gsaturates\u001b[80Ga\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B1/2.5/5GbE devstation link outright. Only a 10GbE link makes the gate\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Binteresting (QUIC w\u001b[23Guld land ~50–80%\u001b[40Gof line rate), and that's \u001b[67Gxac\u001b[71Gly\u001b[74Gwhat\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bthe LAN le\u001b[15Gdecides when the\u001b[32Gdevstati\u001b[41Gn\u001b[43Gis onlin\u001b[52G.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- \u001b[1mThe rustls-TCP reference lane did its job:\u001b[22m crypto\u001b[55Galone\u001b[61Gcosts\u001b[67G~45%\u001b[72G(plain\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BTCP 253 → TLS-TCP 142 Gbps at N=16/64KB), so\u001b[48GQUIC's\u001b[55Gremaining gap is\u001b[72G\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Btransport-structural (per-d\u001b[32Gagram userspace\u001b[48Gwork),\u001b[55Gnot crypto. QUIC's\u001b[74Gp50\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Blatency (17µs) sits at TLS-TCP level.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- One real finding for\u001b[26Gthe fold: \u001b[1mQUIC throughput doesn't scale with stream \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bcount\u001b[9G\u001b[22m(N=1\u001b[14Gbeats N=16 — one connection = one crypto/pacing pipeline).\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BIrrelevant\u001b[14Gwhen link-capped, but i\u001b[38G's the p\u001b[47Gr-connection ceiling to remember.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BAnd\u001b[7Gto\u001b[10Gclose\u001b[16Gthe\u001b[20Gloop\u001b[25Gon\u001b[56Gstems\u001b[62Gall\u001b[66Gkeep\u001b[71Gworking.\u001b[23;1H\u001b[19;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
[33072.56766, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Binteresting (QUIC would land ~50–80%\u001b[40Gof\u001b[43Gline\u001b[48Grate),\u001b[55Gand\u001b[59Gthat's\u001b[66Gexactly\u001b[74Gwhat\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bthe LAN leg decides when the devstation is online.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- \u001b[1mThe rustls-TCP reference lane did its job:\u001b[22m crypto alone cos\u001b[65Gs ~45% (plain\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BTCP 253 → TLS-TCP\u001b[21G142 Gbps at N=16/64KB), so\u001b[48GQUIC's\u001b[55Gremaining gap is\u001b[K\r\u001b[3C\u001b[1Bransport-stru\u001b[18Gtural (per-datagram userspace work),\u001b[55Gnot\u001b[59Gcrypto.\u001b[67GQUIC's\u001b[74Gp50\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Blatency (17µs) sits at TLS-TCP level.\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B- One real finding for the\u001b[30Gfold: \u001b[1mQUIC throughput doesn't scale with stream \r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bcount\u001b[22m (N=1 beats N=16 — one connection = on\u001b[48Gcrypto/pacing \u001b[63Gipeline).\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BIrr\u001b[7Glevant when link-capped, but it's\u001b[41Gthe\u001b[45Gper-connection\u001b[60Gceiling\u001b[68Gto\u001b[71Gremember.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BAnd to close the\u001b[20Gloop\u001b[25Gon your qu\u001b[36Gs\u001b[41G: yes — your systems\u001b[62Gall keep working.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BThe embedded high-performance ingestion nev\u001b[48G leav\u001b[54Gs clyffy; the\u001b[68Gwire only\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bdelivers\u001b[12Gcontext,\u001b[21Gthe\u001b[25Gmeasured\u001b[34Gfloor\u001b[40Gis\u001b[43Gorders\u001b[50Gof\u001b[53Gmagnitude\u001b[63Gabove\u001b[69Gwhat\u001b[74Gthe\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bpipeline consum\u001b[19Gs, and j\u001b[58G a b\u001b[63Gd connection can\u001b[23;1H\u001b[19;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
[33072.586511, "o", "\u001b[?2026h\u001b[?25l\u001b[H\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BAnd\u001b[7Gto c\u001b[12Gose the loop o\u001b[28Gyour question:\u001b[43Gyes — your\u001b[54Gsystems\u001b[62Gall\u001b[66Gkeep\u001b[71Gworking.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BThe embedded high-performance ingestion never leaves clyffy; \u001b[65Ghe wire only\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bdelivers context,\u001b[21Gthe\u001b[25Gmea\u001b[29Gured floor is orders of magnitude above\u001b[69Gwhat\u001b[74Gthe\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bpipeline cons\u001b[17Gmes, and journal-then-ACK means the wors\u001b[59Ga bad connection can\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bdo is delay \u001b[3mnew\u001b[23m context — it can n\u001b[38Gver\u001b[42Gstall\u001b[48Gor\u001b[51Gdegrade\u001b[59Gclyffy\u001b[66Gitself.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BOnly the real-LAN leg\u001b[25G(devstation ↔ clyffy-01) remains, and \u001b[64Gt needs the\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bdevstation\u001b[14Gp\u001b[16Gysically online\u001b[32G— it's recorded as th\u001b[54G ope\u001b[60Ggate cell in the\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1Bnotes\u001b[9Gfor\u001b[13Gthe\u001b[17Gfold.\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1BYou\u001b[7Gcan close this session now — that trigg\u001b[48Gs branch 4 (deployment-shape).\r\u001b[2C\u001b[1B\u001b[K\r\u001b[1B\u001b[38;5;246m✻\u001b[3GSautéed for 1m 14s\u001b[22G\u001b[39m\u001b[K\u001b[23;1H\u001b[19;3H\u001b[?25h\u001b[?2026l"]
